1st January 2025
Last Updated:
1st January 2025
1. Who We Are
cr0bar Limited ("we," "us," "our") is a company registered in England and Wales with company number 07332447. Our registered office is at 124-128 City Road, London, EC1V 2NX.
We are registered with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) under registration reference
ZA902799
. If you have any questions about this privacy policy or how we process your personal data, you can contact our Data Protection Officer:
Data Protection Officer (DPO):
Anthony de Broise
Email:
dpo@cr0.bar
Phone: +44 33 3339 3331
2. What Personal Data We Collect
We may collect and process the following personal data:
Contact Information:
Name, address, email address, and phone number.
Identification Data:
Date of birth, government-issued ID (if applicable).
Payment Information:
Credit card details or bank account information for transactions.
Usage Data:
Information about how you use our website, products, and services.
Technical Data:
IP address, browser type, operating system, and other technical details.
3. How We Collect Your Data
We collect personal data:
Directly from you:
When you interact with us (e.g., filling out forms, emailing us, or making a purchase).
Automatically:
Through cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website.
From third parties:
Such as business partners, analytics providers, or publicly available sources.
4. Legal Basis for Processing
We process your personal data under the following legal bases:
Consent:
When you provide your explicit consent for specific purposes.
Contract:
To perform or enter into a contract with you.
Legal Obligation:
To comply with legal or regulatory obligations.
Legitimate Interests:
To improve our services, prevent fraud, and protect our business.
5. How We Use Your Data
We use your personal data for the following purposes:
Providing and managing our services.
Processing transactions and payments.
Communicating with you (e.g., updates, newsletters, or customer support).
Improving our website and services through analytics.
Complying with legal and regulatory requirements.
6. Sharing Your Data
We may share your personal data with:
Service providers and business partners who assist us in delivering our services.
Legal authorities, if required by law or to protect our legal rights.
Third parties in the event of a business transfer, merger, or acquisition.
7. International Data Transfers
Your personal data may be transferred to and stored in countries outside the UK or EEA. We ensure that any such transfer complies with applicable data protection laws and that appropriate safeguards, such as standard contractual clauses, are in place.
8. Data Retention
We will retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes we collected it for, including for legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.
9. Your Rights
Under the UK GDPR and EU GDPR, you have the following rights:
Access:
To request access to your personal data.
Rectification:
To correct inaccurate or incomplete data.
Erasure:
To request the deletion of your data in certain circumstances.
Restriction:
To request restricted processing of your data.
Portability:
To receive your data in a structured, commonly used format.
Objection:
To object to data processing based on legitimate interests or direct marketing.
Withdraw Consent:
To withdraw your consent at any time.
To exercise your rights, please contact our DPO at
dpo@cr0.bar
.
10. Cookies
We use cookies to enhance your experience on our website. For more information, see our Cookie Policy.
11. Security Measures
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse.
12. Complaints
If you have concerns about our handling of your data, you can contact us at
dpo@cr0.bar
. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the ICO:
Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)
Website:
www.ico.org.uk
Phone: +44 303 123 1113
13. Changes to This Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on our website.
